  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hands for life: Neonatology for newborns in Benin</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project &quot;Hands for life&quot; aims at the construction of a neonatology department in the pediatric hospital L&apos;Abbraccio in Sokponta (Benin).This structure will be used to monitor the health of infants who are premature, underweight or have specific infections or malformations and to make women aware of the importance of receiving medical treatment during and after gestation.Furthermore we want to implement health awareness activities in rural villages to prevent infectious disease and Covid-19.</narrative>
  </description>
